quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  8,53,"“And God will never change the favor which He has bestowed on a people until they change what is in themselves, and indeed God is He Who hears and knows all things.”"
  8,54,"The way of the people of Pharaoh and those before them, is that they treated the signs of their Lord as false. So We caused them to perish for their wrongdoing, and We drowned the people of Pharaoh, for they were all oppressors and wrongdoers"
  8,55,For the worst of creatures in the sight of God are those who reject Him and will not believe
  8,56,"They are those with whom you have made a covenant, but they break their covenant every time, because they are not regardful"
  8,57,"If you gain an advantage over them in war, then remind those who follow them, so they may consider"
  8,58,"If you fear treachery from any group, throw back their covenant to them, in order to be on equal terms, for God does not love the treacherous"
  8,59,"Do not let the unbelievers think that they can get the better of you, they will never prevail"
  8,60,"Against them, make your strength ready to the utmost of your power, including steeds of war, to strike fear into the hearts of the enemies of God, who are also your enemies, and others besides you, whom you may not know, but whom God knows. Whatever you give in the cause of God will be repaid to you, and you will not be treated unjustly"
  8,61,"But if the enemy reaches out for peace, you should reach out for peace, and trust in God, for He is One who hears and knows all things"